race.comment: SUZE SPRITZ (13) raced on the speed when resuming last start and battled on well but found one better over 1000m at Penshurst. Going well enough to take this out with the added fitness from that run. ANTALIAN (8) was out of the money when resuming two runs back then again missed the frame last start over 1200m at Mornington, beaten 2 lengths into fifth but this is probably easier than recent runs, so gets the chance to break the run of fifths. IMPACTICAL (15) ran a nice race on debut in a slightly easier race than this but will be better for it and draws beautifully here. GRAN PARADISO (4) did little on debut but has jumped out well since so can improve.
